Public Safety Power Shutoff Updates (10/9/2019 @ 2:00 p.m.) - Based on the most recent information we have from PG&E regarding the Public Safety Power Shutoff (PSPS), all CVUSD schools will be open tomorrow, Thursday, October 10.

As of 1 p.m. today, PG&E has pushed back the shutoff to 8 p.m. tonight in Alameda County. Please keep in mind that, as we have seen, this information is fluid based on changing weather conditions. PG&E is making the decisions for its customers. Jensen Ranch, Palomares, and Proctor Elementary Schools and Canyon Middle School were on the list to have their power shut off, those schools were closed today. However, PG&E did not shut off power at any CVUSD schools today.

Please plan on having your children attend school tomorrow with a contingency plan in case we have to close schools due to a power shutoff.

The safety of our students and staff remains our first priority. We will continue to provide updated information as it becomes available to us via emails, texts, and the website. http://edl.io/n1102014

post_text:
We recently reached out to our community to seek feedback about Castro Valley schools and priorities for maintaining strong academic programs and preparing students for success. We sent out a survey through the mail and also provided an online version as well. our community noted retaining and attracting highly qualified teachers, preserving strong academic programs and preparing students for college and careers as top priorities.

With these priorities in mind, the Board of Education is considering placing a local funding measure on an upcoming ballot. As we explore funding options, we still want to hear from you! Please visit www.cv.k12.ca.us/localfunding/ to learn more and take our online survey.
